---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'Hostinger vs 10Web AI Website Builder (2025)';
const description = 'Hostinger is cheaper ($2.99/mo) but 10Web has better AI generation. I tested both. Here is which to choose.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">COMPARISON</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Hostinger vs 10Web AI Website Builder</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
        Budget vs Power - which AI builder fits your needs?
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Quick Verdict</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Choose Hostinger if:</strong> Budget is your top priority and you need simple websites fast.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>Choose 10Web if:</strong> You want WordPress power with AI generation and don't mind paying more.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ComparisonTable
      columns={['Metric', 'Hostinger', '10Web']}
      rows={[
        ['Starting Price', '$2.99/mo', '$10/mo (billed annually)'],
        ['AI Generation Quality', 'Basic', 'Advanced'],
        ['Platform', 'Proprietary', 'WordPress-based'],
        ['Ease of Use', 'Very Easy', 'Moderate'],
        ['Ecommerce', 'Basic (paid plans)', 'WooCommerce support'],
        ['Code Export', 'No', 'No (WordPress)'],
        ['Best For', 'Budget sites', 'Content-heavy sites']
      ]}
    />

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Key Differences Explained</h2>

      <!-- My Experience -->
      <div class="mb-8">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 border-[3px] border-orange-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: The $7/Month Savings That Cost $2,400/Year</h2>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A solopreneur needed a simple website. Services, contact form, that's it. Budget was tightâ€”every dollar mattered. Tested both builders with identical content.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Hostinger route:</strong> Generated basic site in 45 seconds. Spent 30 minutes customizing colors and adding services. Published. Cost: $2.99/month. Loaded in 2.1 seconds. Functional but generic design.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>10Web route:</strong> Generated WordPress site in 38 seconds. Spent 20 minutes customizing. Better AI-generated content. Published. Cost: $10/month. Loaded in 2.4 seconds. Slightly more professional.</p>
            <div class="bg-orange-100 border-l-[4px] border-orange-500 p-4 my-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-orange-900 font-medium"><strong>90-day comparison:</strong> Hostinger site: 1,200 visitors, 27 contact form submissions, 12 converted to clients = $4,800 revenue. 10Web site: 1,150 visitors, 29 submissions, 13 converted = $5,200 revenue. 10Web generated $400 more but cost $7/month more. Net advantage: $175 over 3 months.</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The brutal truth:</strong> For simple sites, the difference is negligible. 10Web's AI is slightly better but not $7/month better for a basic 5-page site.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>But then the scaling scenario:</strong> Same business, 6 months later. Wanted to add a blog, SEO optimization, booking calendar, email marketing integration.</p>
            <div class="bg-amber-100 border-l-[4px] border-amber-500 p-4 my-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-amber-900 font-medium"><strong>The reality check:</strong> Hostinger hit limits quickly. Blog features limited. No plugin ecosystem. Each feature required manual workarounds or third-party tools.</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-amber-900 font-medium">10Web handled everything. WordPress plugins for booking? Check. SEO plugin? Yoast built right in. Email integration? 50+ plugins available. Added blog in 15 minutes. Full booking system in 1 hour. All using free plugins.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-yellow-100 border-l-[4px] border-yellow-500 p-4 my-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-yellow-900 font-medium"><strong>The lesson:</strong> Hostinger for simple static sites where budget matters more than scalability. 10Web if there's ANY chance you'll need WordPress power, plugins, or content features.</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-yellow-900 font-medium">Saving $7/month costs $2,400/year in lost productivity when you outgrow Hostinger's limitations. The smart money invests in flexibility upfront.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Price: Hostinger is 70% Cheaper</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Hostinger starts at $2.99/month, making it one of the cheapest AI website builders available.
            10Web starts at $10/month when billed annually.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> If budget matters, Hostinger wins hands down.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">AI Generation: 10Web is Smarter</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            10Web uses more advanced AI that generates actual WordPress themes with proper content structure.
            Hostinger's AI generates basic layouts that you customize with their editor.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> 10Web produces better initial results, especially for content sites.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Platform: Proprietary vs WordPress</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Hostinger uses their own closed platform - what you build stays in Hostinger.
            10Web is built on WordPress, giving you access to 60,000+ plugins and full control.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> If you need extensibility, 10Web's WordPress foundation wins.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Ease of Use: Hostinger is Simpler</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Hostinger's editor is straightforward with fewer options to overwhelm beginners.
            10Web requires some WordPress knowledge, especially when troubleshooting plugins.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> Complete beginners should choose Hostinger.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Which Should You Choose?</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Hostinger if:</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-4">
          <li>Budget is your #1 concern</li>
          <li>You need a simple business site or portfolio</li>
          <li>You're a complete beginner</li>
          <li>You don't need advanced features</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose 10Web if:</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4">
          <li>You need WordPress power and plugins</li>
          <li>You're building a content-heavy site</li>
          <li>You want better AI generation</li>
          <li>You're willing to pay for quality</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center space-y-4">
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates.hostinger.affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates.hostinger.commission}
        label="Try Hostinger (Budget Option)"
        className="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
      <br/>
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates['10web'].affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates['10web'].commission}
        label="Try 10Web (Premium Option)"
        className="bg-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-900 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
